main event: A long, narrow white object with two flashing lights in the center was observed for 4-5 minutes, flying in a straight easterly direction at level flight.
interesting points: The object appeared to have a long row of windows that looked longer than a commercial jet airliner, but it did not have any visible wings.
The object was observed from the ground and did not make any sound.
The sighting occurred on February 27, 1967 in Wheatridge, Colorado.
The report states that no data was presented to indicate the object could not have been an aircraft.
The report concludes that the object was an aircraft, despite the unusual features described.
